Wed Apr 8 2026
- Implemented the write_board_to_file() function for task5 in func.c to write the current board state to an output file.
- This function is similar to the load_from_file() in terms of code flow but instead writes the current board structure to a file in the same format as the input file.
- Trimming the leading spaces in the input file is added to the load_from_file() function to not have issue with displaying the board and output file format.
- In print_welcome(), scanf() flushing is added to handle non-integer input and to avoid infinite loop and defaults to -1.
- tmp variable is added in main.c to avoid updating if the file loading failed.
- Ascii art function is implemented and added to main.c
- The previous func.c was further modularized into io.c, board.c and editor.c for better readability.
- io.c will handle file input and output, board.c will handle the board display and menu as well as predefined board, and editor.c will handle the editing of the board (Task 3 and Task 4).
